1
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:33,821
The girl is born.

2
00:02:34,155 --> 00:02:35,364
This joy shall fill the world.

3
00:03:23,829 --> 00:03:30,711
SADAKO 2 -3D-

4
00:03:32,004 --> 00:03:36,133
Five Years Later

5
00:03:40,095 --> 00:03:48,729
Kagome, Kagome, the bird in the cage,
when, when will you come out?

6
00:03:49,021 --> 00:03:57,112
In the evening of the dawn,
the crane and turtle slipped.

7
00:03:57,321 --> 00:04:01,450
Who stands right behind you now?

8
00:04:21,679 --> 00:04:23,806
Look, Nagi's all alone.

9
00:05:14,606 --> 00:05:17,609
Hello? How is it?

10
00:05:21,780 --> 00:05:25,617
Oh, I see...

11
00:05:28,620 --> 00:05:33,292
I get it. Okay, I'll be waiting.

12
00:05:38,213 --> 00:05:39,798
What? A girl's voice?

13
00:05:43,719 --> 00:05:44,762
Huh?

14
00:05:44,845 --> 00:05:46,555
There's no child here.

15
00:05:51,477 --> 00:05:52,519
Okay, bye.

16
00:06:42,611 --> 00:06:43,404
No!

17
00:07:43,255 --> 00:07:46,967
Yuki Kindergarten

18
00:08:00,689 --> 00:08:04,067
My mommy's coming for me soon.

19
00:08:05,777 --> 00:08:07,321
Your mommy, Nagi?

20
00:08:09,823 --> 00:08:11,825
Why's she never here?

21
00:08:14,495 --> 00:08:16,538
Is she dead?

22
00:08:21,043 --> 00:08:22,836
Say something!

23
00:08:35,224 --> 00:08:36,892
Nagi, for you.

24
00:08:37,017 --> 00:08:38,560
Fuko's here.

25
00:08:51,657 --> 00:08:55,953
What did you do today? Draw pictures?

26
00:09:01,542 --> 00:09:03,835
Is she your friend?

27
00:09:04,336 --> 00:09:06,171
What's her name?

28
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:15,180
What do you want to eat?

29
00:09:24,690 --> 00:09:29,069
Hello? Where you at? Movie theater?

30
00:09:29,403 --> 00:09:32,614
Why YOU picking up then?

31
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:37,786
Anyway, about that. You see...

32
00:09:41,582 --> 00:09:42,583
What?

33
00:09:46,086 --> 00:09:48,797
- What?
- Sorry.

34
00:09:50,424 --> 00:09:51,258
I'm sorry.

35
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:52,801
What's wrong, Nagi?

36
00:09:53,176 --> 00:09:55,012
A weird kid grabbed me.

37
00:09:55,095 --> 00:09:56,471
Let's go.

38
00:09:56,555 --> 00:09:58,348
You sure?

39
00:10:14,990 --> 00:10:20,078
Asakawa General Hospital

40
00:11:03,497 --> 00:11:03,955
Hey!

41
00:11:04,956 --> 00:11:08,168
Ando, there you are.

42
00:11:09,544 --> 00:11:15,342
A power problem at the nurses' station.
Go check it out.

43
00:11:16,802 --> 00:11:17,886
Okay.

44
00:11:21,264 --> 00:11:22,265
Hey-

45
00:11:22,724 --> 00:11:26,895
By the way, your sister called just now.

46
00:11:27,437 --> 00:11:29,564
Get a mobile already.

47
00:11:31,191 --> 00:11:32,609
Sorry.

48
00:12:19,865 --> 00:12:22,743
Aren't you hungry?

49
00:12:28,331 --> 00:12:32,043
I know, how about some rice balls?

50
00:12:36,673 --> 00:12:39,384
I want Mom to cook for me.

51
00:12:45,223 --> 00:12:51,688
Nagi, your mother isn't here anymore.

52
00:13:21,551 --> 00:13:23,512
Hello? Takanori?

53
00:13:25,430 --> 00:13:26,598
You called?

54
00:13:29,226 --> 00:13:31,520
Yeah. Nothing urgent, but...

55
00:13:32,187 --> 00:13:33,980
- Today...
- How's Nagi?

56
00:13:39,528 --> 00:13:41,822
Uh, well...

57
00:13:41,905 --> 00:13:43,490
- She enjoyed her dinner I...
- I see.

58
00:14:28,368 --> 00:14:30,328
The psych test result:

59
00:14:30,412 --> 00:14:33,290
instability and introversion.

60
00:14:33,832 --> 00:14:34,749
Well done.

61
00:14:36,209 --> 00:14:38,879
Now on the three steps of
psychotherapy used in Counseling:

62
00:14:38,962 --> 00:14:43,550
psychoanalysis, Rogerian approach and
cognitive-behavioral therapy.

63
00:14:49,890 --> 00:14:55,478
In psychoanalysis, you dig deep
into the patient's mind.

64
00:14:55,562 --> 00:15:00,650
To look for traumatic experiences
they may be suppressing.

65
00:15:09,367 --> 00:15:23,006
Nagi...doesn't know Akane. Her long
lost mother. She died after giving birth.

66
00:15:26,301 --> 00:15:31,306
But of course, I can't be Nagi's mother.
Nagi has this emptiness in her heart.

67
00:15:33,975 --> 00:15:39,689
Hence, the drawings.

68
00:15:42,609 --> 00:15:44,277
Just relax.

69
00:15:45,654 --> 00:15:52,035
Children her age have a wild imagination
we adults can't imagine.

70
00:15:52,494 --> 00:15:53,745
Still...

71
00:16:00,293 --> 00:16:01,211
Here.

72
00:16:14,557 --> 00:16:15,600
Ando,

73
00:16:18,395 --> 00:16:19,145
aren't you just

74
00:16:20,230 --> 00:16:24,109
projecting yourself onto Nagi?

75
00:16:29,739 --> 00:16:33,451
You lost your mother to suicide.

76
00:16:35,203 --> 00:16:41,251
Children like to blame
themselves to ease their pain.

77
00:16:43,086 --> 00:16:47,966
You're still blaming yourself
for your mother.

78
00:16:54,806 --> 00:16:57,308
Stopped dreaming about her?

79
00:16:59,769 --> 00:17:00,603
Yes.

80
00:17:05,483 --> 00:17:07,110
I see.

81
00:17:17,871 --> 00:17:18,705
Then don't worry.

82
00:17:18,788 --> 00:17:22,125
You can bring her anytime. Nagi, I mean.

83
00:17:36,931 --> 00:17:40,351
I've had enough.
Sure, they pay me but still!

84
00:17:40,685 --> 00:17:41,728
Right?

85
00:17:46,775 --> 00:17:48,443
So creepy.

86
00:17:56,493 --> 00:17:58,036
Let's see...

87
00:18:01,831 --> 00:18:03,750
Seiji Kashiwada arrested

88
00:18:03,833 --> 00:18:07,295
for multiple murder five years ago.

89
00:18:07,629 --> 00:18:11,633
The verdict was announced today
without his testimony.

90
00:18:12,342 --> 00:18:15,887
Kashiwada kidnapped and murdered
a number of women around Tokyo,

91
00:18:15,970 --> 00:18:18,765
disposing their bodies in a well.

92
00:18:57,929 --> 00:19:02,267
So, why isn't your mommy here, Nagi?

93
00:19:05,145 --> 00:19:07,021
Tell me, why?

94
00:19:16,156 --> 00:19:17,198
Let's go.

95
00:19:33,423 --> 00:19:43,516
Kagome, Kagome, the bird in the cage...

96
00:19:43,641 --> 00:19:51,024
Who stands right behind you now?

97
00:20:34,943 --> 00:20:36,027
Yuna!

98
00:20:37,403 --> 00:20:39,155
Yuna! Yuna!

99
00:20:40,823 --> 00:20:43,910
Yuna!

100
00:20:45,745 --> 00:20:50,291
Yuna!

101
00:21:07,141 --> 00:21:08,643
Nagi?

102
00:21:09,310 --> 00:21:10,687
Nagi?

103
00:22:25,553 --> 00:22:29,682
Cut it out. Don't point the flash at me!

104
00:22:29,766 --> 00:22:31,225
Sorry, sir.

105
00:22:43,279 --> 00:22:47,742
Hey. You okay, Kakiuchi? Are you ready?

106
00:22:49,786 --> 00:22:52,163
I'm fine, sir.

107
00:22:54,082 --> 00:22:55,625
May I?

108
00:23:14,394 --> 00:23:17,230
Sure. She cut
her own tongue off.

109
00:23:18,606 --> 00:23:19,148
Smashed that

110
00:23:19,232 --> 00:23:20,608
and committed suicide.

111
00:23:22,485 --> 00:23:26,489
So many messed up
suicides lately.

112
00:23:28,699 --> 00:23:30,034
I mean...

113
00:23:31,035 --> 00:23:32,620
Huh?

114
00:23:40,378 --> 00:23:41,712
This here...

115
00:23:43,881 --> 00:23:46,134
She had a kid over?

116
00:23:48,928 --> 00:23:49,804
Maybe...

117
00:23:50,805 --> 00:23:52,723
The cursed video clip?

118
00:23:52,807 --> 00:23:53,766
What?

119
00:23:54,559 --> 00:23:58,354
Huh? No, never mind. Excuse me, sir.

120
00:24:01,232 --> 00:24:03,693
Fuko, I've had enough!

121
00:24:03,776 --> 00:24:07,155
I do have a life, too, you know?

122
00:24:07,238 --> 00:24:07,864
Sorry,

123
00:24:07,947 --> 00:24:10,199
Ms. Igarashi. I'm close.

124
00:24:10,867 --> 00:24:12,201
I'm leaving!

125
00:24:15,830 --> 00:24:16,831
Hey you!

126
00:24:18,875 --> 00:24:22,712
Hands off that. It's not for kids.

127
00:24:24,505 --> 00:24:26,257
What?

128
00:24:36,100 --> 00:24:38,060
I'm leaving now.

129
00:24:40,438 --> 00:24:42,607
What's with her?

130
00:25:15,973 --> 00:25:20,102
Nagi!

131
00:25:20,186 --> 00:25:24,732
Nagi! Nagi! Nagi!

132
00:25:58,849 --> 00:26:01,060
Thank you for coming.

133
00:26:02,019 --> 00:26:05,940
Kakiuchi of the Metropolitan Police.

134
00:26:08,276 --> 00:26:11,362
We finally meet, Mr. Koiso.

135
00:26:21,122 --> 00:26:25,876
Those who see something on
an electronic device commit suicide.

136
00:26:26,586 --> 00:26:28,963
Just like your case.

137
00:26:29,046 --> 00:26:31,257
It's happening all over again.

138
00:26:38,431 --> 00:26:41,392
What's the "cursed video clip"?

139
00:26:44,061 --> 00:26:46,522
Why do those who watch die?

140
00:26:49,442 --> 00:26:54,572
People with absolutely
no reason to die have died.

141
00:27:00,369 --> 00:27:02,246
Who made it?

142
00:27:02,913 --> 00:27:05,916
Why is it killing people again?

143
00:27:14,008 --> 00:27:15,843
Sadako.

144
00:27:20,389 --> 00:27:22,266
Sadako...?

145
00:27:26,270 --> 00:27:34,528
A girl who died decades ago.
She was different, had special powers.

146
00:27:35,112 --> 00:27:40,076
But she was feared by others for that.

147
00:27:40,493 --> 00:27:44,497
She was thrown into a well alive.

148
00:27:50,878 --> 00:27:57,551
What's a girl who died decades ago
have to do with a deadly video clip?

149
00:28:03,683 --> 00:28:05,810
A deep grudge-

150
00:28:14,985 --> 00:28:20,741
Is there anyone else
who was involved in the case?

151
00:28:23,202 --> 00:28:26,706
Akane Ayukawa.

152
00:28:27,832 --> 00:28:33,045
Akane Ayukawa? Who's that?

153
00:28:34,171 --> 00:28:40,594
A woman whose body Sadako desired.

154
00:28:43,347 --> 00:28:49,812
Mr. Koiso,
I don't get a thing you're saying!

155
00:28:56,152 --> 00:28:58,112
Thank you, sir.

156
00:29:14,628 --> 00:29:15,713
Sadako...

157
00:29:34,690 --> 00:29:38,068
Laboratory No. 11
Fumika Kamimura

158
00:30:04,261 --> 00:30:05,846
Who's that?

159
00:30:17,817 --> 00:30:19,819
Why are you drawing it?

160
00:30:22,530 --> 00:30:24,114
Cos you'll die.

161
00:30:24,573 --> 00:30:25,407
What?

162
00:30:43,008 --> 00:30:44,677
You're lonely.

163
00:30:46,804 --> 00:30:50,349
You draw to forget your loneliness

164
00:30:50,432 --> 00:30:52,101
about your mother.

165
00:30:56,146 --> 00:30:59,066
I can understand your loneliness.

166
00:31:02,027 --> 00:31:04,113
No, you're lonely.

167
00:31:05,739 --> 00:31:09,410
No one's there. You're always alone.

168
00:31:10,494 --> 00:31:16,250
You're devoting yourself
to work to forget that.

169
00:31:30,764 --> 00:31:32,182
You scared?

170
00:31:34,894 --> 00:31:36,437
Scared of me?

171
00:31:37,813 --> 00:31:39,648
No, I'm...

172
00:31:46,530 --> 00:31:48,157
Everyone will die.

173
00:31:59,877 --> 00:32:01,545
Professor?

174
00:32:06,926 --> 00:32:07,843
Here.

175
00:32:22,358 --> 00:32:24,109
She's a great girl.

176
00:32:26,904 --> 00:32:34,119
She has the signs of a parentless child.
Blaming herself a bit.

177
00:32:36,413 --> 00:32:38,749
But she'll get over it.

178
00:32:41,210 --> 00:32:42,252
Yes...

179
00:32:51,595 --> 00:32:53,847
She's such a sweet girl.

180
00:32:56,600 --> 00:32:58,310
A nice girl.

181
00:33:14,368 --> 00:33:15,619
Nagi?

182
00:33:18,789 --> 00:33:19,999
Nagi!

183
00:33:21,291 --> 00:33:22,960
A train is arriving.

184
00:33:23,669 --> 00:33:27,464
Please stay behind the yellow line.

185
00:33:38,517 --> 00:33:39,893
Doors are closing.

186
00:33:40,269 --> 00:33:44,648
Please stand clear and
wait for the next train.

187
00:34:48,962 --> 00:34:55,928
Nagi!

188
00:35:23,622 --> 00:35:24,706
This way.

189
00:35:35,509 --> 00:35:40,973
Stand back! Let us through!

190
00:36:25,350 --> 00:36:27,227
You know it.

191
00:36:31,940 --> 00:36:34,151
You know, right?

192
00:36:37,404 --> 00:36:38,822
Know what?

193
00:36:40,657 --> 00:36:43,952
Too many disasters around her.

194
00:36:48,624 --> 00:36:50,709
The kindergarten girl,

195
00:36:50,792 --> 00:36:54,338
Ms. Igarashi... The train, too.

196
00:36:59,384 --> 00:37:01,678
Nagi's always there.

197
00:37:08,185 --> 00:37:09,686
Why?

198
00:37:12,940 --> 00:37:17,277
I'm scared of Nagi.

199
00:37:19,780 --> 00:37:26,620
I'm more scared of you for saying that.

200
00:37:35,629 --> 00:37:37,547
She's causing them, isn't she?

201
00:37:37,631 --> 00:37:41,134
Who is she, really?

202
00:37:47,224 --> 00:37:50,811
Is she really yours and Akane's child?

203
00:40:41,940 --> 00:40:45,944
Mr. Ando? Takanori Ando?

204
00:40:50,323 --> 00:40:51,992
Who's asking?

205
00:40:56,037 --> 00:40:58,373
Kakiuchi of the Metropolitan Police.

206
00:40:58,790 --> 00:41:00,876
Mr. Koiso told me.

207
00:41:04,379 --> 00:41:07,257
Where is Akane Ayukawa?

208
00:41:16,558 --> 00:41:19,478
Akane died...

209
00:41:20,770 --> 00:41:23,148
Sorry to hear that.

210
00:41:24,107 --> 00:41:25,525
Is that it?

211
00:41:28,904 --> 00:41:31,573
Akane Ayukawa had a daughter?

212
00:41:35,076 --> 00:41:37,871
She's such a cute girl.

213
00:41:38,872 --> 00:41:40,415
How old is she?

214
00:41:41,291 --> 00:41:42,959
Around four?

215
00:41:45,003 --> 00:41:46,463
I'm in a hurry.

216
00:44:02,599 --> 00:44:05,727
To Takanori Ando

217
00:44:09,022 --> 00:44:10,565
How is Nagi?

218
00:44:12,317 --> 00:44:18,031
How is Nagi? How is Nagi?

219
00:44:45,850 --> 00:44:50,146
Seiji Kashiwada

220
00:44:50,271 --> 00:44:56,319
Kashiwada... Seiji...?

221
00:46:30,413 --> 00:46:32,332
Fuko Ando.

222
00:46:50,725 --> 00:46:53,853
How do you know who I am?

223
00:46:58,358 --> 00:47:00,068
How is Nagi?

224
00:47:04,614 --> 00:47:07,158
How do you know Nagi?

225
00:47:08,034 --> 00:47:10,119
And your letters?

226
00:47:12,288 --> 00:47:14,541
I am Nagi's fan.

227
00:47:17,210 --> 00:47:19,045
What?

228
00:47:24,634 --> 00:47:26,344
You're scared.

229
00:47:29,180 --> 00:47:30,974
Scared?

230
00:47:32,934 --> 00:47:34,519
Of what?

231
00:47:39,023 --> 00:47:40,817
Nagi.

232
00:47:47,282 --> 00:47:49,951
Saw the cursed video clip?

233
00:47:52,245 --> 00:47:54,205
What clip?

234
00:48:02,881 --> 00:48:05,717
Not yet, it seems.

235
00:48:09,178 --> 00:48:12,849
Nagi likes you, perhaps.

236
00:48:14,267 --> 00:48:16,144
What do you mean?

237
00:48:20,148 --> 00:48:22,191
You watch, you die.

238
00:48:31,451 --> 00:48:34,787
You came to me for help, right?

239
00:48:36,915 --> 00:48:37,832
What?

240
00:48:38,958 --> 00:48:42,128
You've always sought Salvation.

241
00:48:42,837 --> 00:48:44,005
No, I...

242
00:48:44,088 --> 00:48:46,090
That's why you came.

243
00:48:46,883 --> 00:48:49,677
Your mother's suicide in the tub.

244
00:48:51,095 --> 00:48:52,138
How...?

245
00:48:52,221 --> 00:48:55,141
You forced her into suicide.

246
00:48:55,642 --> 00:48:58,102
When she needed help.

247
00:48:58,353 --> 00:48:59,187
Stop...

248
00:48:59,270 --> 00:49:02,523
You couldn't help your mother.

249
00:49:02,607 --> 00:49:04,025
Stop Â¡t!

250
00:49:12,492 --> 00:49:14,911
I got off track.

251
00:49:23,252 --> 00:49:24,837
Nagi...

252
00:49:26,673 --> 00:49:28,758
Who is she?

253
00:49:30,969 --> 00:49:33,763
You think she's really Akane's?

254
00:49:36,265 --> 00:49:38,476
What do you mean?

255
00:49:41,104 --> 00:49:43,731
If Nagi's not Akane's,

256
00:49:43,815 --> 00:49:46,359
whose child is she?

257
00:49:51,197 --> 00:49:52,490
Sadako.

258
00:49:54,283 --> 00:49:55,910
Sadako?

259
00:49:57,578 --> 00:49:59,122
Who is she?

260
00:50:01,666 --> 00:50:03,292
Despair.

261
00:50:06,212 --> 00:50:11,092
Five years ago,
she sowed the seed of despair.

262
00:50:12,802 --> 00:50:15,847
With the cursed video clip.

263
00:50:18,141 --> 00:50:28,151
And the seed of despair kept growing,
now budding, ready to bloom.

264
00:50:30,069 --> 00:50:31,821
That's...

265
00:50:33,614 --> 00:50:36,034
Sadako's child.

266
00:50:38,327 --> 00:50:40,621
Sadako's child?

267
00:50:48,004 --> 00:50:50,923
You'll live that terror.

268
00:50:51,257 --> 00:50:52,258
No...

269
00:50:53,426 --> 00:50:55,428
You already have.

270
00:50:59,098 --> 00:51:03,144
I know two ways to end that terror.

271
00:51:07,940 --> 00:51:09,817
Want to hear?

272
00:51:23,706 --> 00:51:25,124
One is...

273
00:51:26,834 --> 00:51:31,005
Fuko, you die.

274
00:51:34,509 --> 00:51:35,593
The other...

275
00:51:37,386 --> 00:51:40,598
Pick the bud, soon to bloom.

276
00:51:44,060 --> 00:51:45,103
You...

277
00:51:47,021 --> 00:51:50,733
...kill Sadako's child.

278
00:51:53,736 --> 00:52:00,952
The terror will keep growing.

279
00:52:54,172 --> 00:52:54,755
Fumika Kamimura

280
00:52:54,839 --> 00:52:55,882
Professor?

281
00:53:35,963 --> 00:53:37,673
Professor?

282
00:53:59,987 --> 00:54:02,573
No!

283
00:55:11,225 --> 00:55:13,894
Why won't you help me?

284
00:55:14,395 --> 00:55:15,313
Mom!

