00:55:15,396 --> 00:55:17,815
Mom!Mom!

286
00:55:18,482 --> 00:55:21,485
Mom!Mom!

287
00:55:22,278 --> 00:55:24,613
Mom!Mom!

288
00:55:24,697 --> 00:55:28,117
Mom!Mom!

289
00:55:28,200 --> 00:55:34,332
Mom!Mom!

290
00:55:34,665 --> 00:55:37,585
Don't go, Mom!

291
00:55:37,668 --> 00:55:38,544
Mom!

292
00:55:59,315 --> 00:56:01,650
Why won't you help me?

293
00:56:18,918 --> 00:56:20,378
Nagi...

294
00:57:55,264 --> 00:57:56,932
Sadako...

295
00:58:00,102 --> 00:58:01,395
Auntie.

296
00:58:07,193 --> 00:58:08,652
I'm hungry-

297
00:58:44,063 --> 00:58:46,023
Why won't you help me?

298
00:58:47,858 --> 00:58:50,027
Why won't you help me?

299
00:58:50,110 --> 00:58:55,866
Why won't you help me?
Why won't you help me?

300
00:58:55,950 --> 00:59:01,830
Why won't you help me?
Why won't you help me?

301
00:59:01,914 --> 00:59:04,166
I'm sorry... So sorry...

302
00:59:04,250 --> 00:59:07,795
Why won't you help me?

303
01:00:59,865 --> 01:01:03,077
Hey, Fuko!

304
01:01:03,160 --> 01:01:05,204
Fuko, what's wrong? Tell me.

305
01:01:05,287 --> 01:01:09,917
- I killed her! I killed Mom!
- Fuko!

306
01:01:10,084 --> 01:01:12,795
Fuko, get a grip!

307
01:01:13,253 --> 01:01:17,299
Mom killed herself! It wasn't your fault!

308
01:01:18,175 --> 01:01:19,385
You were small,

309
01:01:19,468 --> 01:01:21,887
but tried to help her.

310
01:01:33,482 --> 01:01:35,192
It's okay, Fuko.

311
01:01:36,110 --> 01:01:41,699
Mom's suicide wasn't your fault.
I know that for sure.

312
01:01:46,620 --> 01:01:48,330
Takanori...

313
01:01:53,043 --> 01:02:00,509
Sorry I left you alone.

314
01:02:02,136 --> 01:02:04,138
Listen, I quit my job.

315
01:02:05,597 --> 01:02:07,933
I'll be with you from now.

316
01:02:10,769 --> 01:02:12,688
So you won't be alone.

317
01:02:16,358 --> 01:02:17,651
Really?

318
01:02:19,695 --> 01:02:24,825
Yeah. Everything will be alright now.

319
01:02:26,952 --> 01:02:28,620
With Mom...

320
01:02:30,247 --> 01:02:32,166
And Nagi, too.

321
01:02:36,545 --> 01:02:40,883
Let's have dinner. Nagi's waiting, too.

322
01:02:51,810 --> 01:02:52,811
Yeah? What is it?

323
01:02:58,901 --> 01:02:59,985
No!

324
01:03:47,866 --> 01:03:52,704
You kill Sadako's child.

325
01:04:45,716 --> 01:04:47,593
Let's go home.

326
01:05:37,142 --> 01:05:39,353
Where are we going?

327
01:05:43,899 --> 01:05:45,400
Auntie?

328
01:08:10,921 --> 01:08:12,464
You'll kill me?

329
01:08:17,010 --> 01:08:19,012
You don't like me?

330
01:08:24,684 --> 01:08:27,521
Why's everyone scared of me?

331
01:08:32,567 --> 01:08:35,153
I want to see Mom.

332
01:08:41,993 --> 01:08:43,578
I'm so sorry...

333
01:08:43,954 --> 01:08:46,456
So sorry...

334
01:08:47,082 --> 01:08:48,875
- Sorry...
- I'm scared.

335
01:08:50,794 --> 01:08:53,713
I can see people's deaths.

336
01:08:55,006 --> 01:08:58,718
Help me, Auntie, help me...

337
01:09:23,910 --> 01:09:30,584
You know, we haven't spoken
like this in ages.

338
01:09:33,420 --> 01:09:38,091
When you're home, you avoid me.

339
01:09:40,302 --> 01:09:41,678
I'm busy.

340
01:09:41,761 --> 01:09:43,263
I need to go.

341
01:09:43,346 --> 01:09:45,557
Nagi needs your help.

342
01:09:52,647 --> 01:09:54,107
Nagi...

343
01:09:55,650 --> 01:09:56,526
She said so.

344
01:10:00,447 --> 01:10:01,907
Nagi...

345
01:10:03,575 --> 01:10:06,119
She may not be ordinary.

346
01:10:07,579 --> 01:10:13,251
But that's not what she wants.

347
01:10:17,005 --> 01:10:22,177
I... I want to help her.

348
01:10:27,265 --> 01:10:29,517
Tell me the truth.

349
01:10:31,311 --> 01:10:32,938
Is Nagi...

350
01:10:34,898 --> 01:10:37,067
...Sadako's child?

351
01:10:57,254 --> 01:10:58,797
Akane...

352
01:11:00,757 --> 01:11:02,259
She's alive.

353
01:12:54,746 --> 01:12:56,289
Five years ago,

354
01:12:56,956 --> 01:12:59,959
Sadako appeared before Akane and I.

355
01:13:01,961 --> 01:13:04,506
Akane has special powers.

356
01:13:06,216 --> 01:13:09,052
Sadako tried to use Akane's body

357
01:13:09,719 --> 01:13:11,388
to be born into this world.

358
01:13:14,099 --> 01:13:15,683
But Akane...

359
01:13:17,394 --> 01:13:20,688
She trapped Sadako in her body.

360
01:13:22,941 --> 01:13:24,317
Soon after,

361
01:13:25,402 --> 01:13:27,320
Akane got pregnant.

362
01:13:30,698 --> 01:13:32,826
That's Nagi?

363
01:13:35,120 --> 01:13:41,334
Akane is still fighting all alone.

364
01:13:46,464 --> 01:13:51,845
Nagi has been drawing Akane's picture.

365
01:14:01,855 --> 01:14:03,273
Nagi has...

366
01:14:05,275 --> 01:14:08,486
...always wanted to see her.

367
01:14:10,196 --> 01:14:11,739
Can't they meet?

368
01:14:12,615 --> 01:14:15,743
No, if Nagi sees Akane,

369
01:14:16,369 --> 01:14:18,663
Sadako will be resurrected.

370
01:14:18,788 --> 01:14:20,373
But that's...

371
01:14:21,458 --> 01:14:23,668
They had to be separated.

372
01:14:25,420 --> 01:14:30,383
That's why Akane...

373
01:14:30,884 --> 01:14:33,303
She has taken on everything
and stayed here.

374
01:14:36,890 --> 01:14:38,766
Akane has been...

375
01:14:40,477 --> 01:14:42,187
...preventing Sadako's power

376
01:14:42,270 --> 01:14:44,898
from reaching Nagi?

377
01:14:46,524 --> 01:14:47,734
Yeah.

378
01:14:48,526 --> 01:14:49,611
Then the recent cases

379
01:14:50,862 --> 01:14:53,656
weren't Nagi's fault?

380
01:14:54,699 --> 01:14:56,826
It's not Nagi.

381
01:14:59,662 --> 01:15:01,539
Then who?

382
01:15:47,210 --> 01:15:50,171
Nagi! Nagi's missing!

383
01:15:50,588 --> 01:15:52,423
Nagi's missing?

384
01:15:57,178 --> 01:15:58,137
Nagi...

385
01:16:01,140 --> 01:16:02,517
Takanori!

386
01:16:09,482 --> 01:16:10,316
Nagi...

387
01:16:23,788 --> 01:16:29,836
So... she is alive?
Akane Ayukawa.

388
01:16:30,962 --> 01:16:32,338
Don't move!

389
01:16:34,841 --> 01:16:36,175
Nagi...

390
01:16:50,857 --> 01:16:53,443
I'll kill them both.

391
01:16:54,235 --> 01:16:56,904
Somebody must end this!

392
01:16:59,407 --> 01:17:01,242
Nagi, run!

393
01:17:14,005 --> 01:17:16,257
Nagi, run!

394
01:17:21,638 --> 01:17:26,225
Nagi... Nagi! Nagi... Run...

395
01:17:39,364 --> 01:17:41,908
Nagi, run!

396
01:18:34,252 --> 01:18:36,254
I said, don't move!

397
01:18:46,431 --> 01:18:47,890
Yeah... me, too...

398
01:18:50,518 --> 01:18:53,104
I finally saw it.

399
01:18:55,148 --> 01:18:57,191
The cursed video clip.

400
01:19:04,782 --> 01:19:06,534
It was her.

401
01:19:09,495 --> 01:19:13,666
My wife was...

402
01:19:19,672 --> 01:19:22,008
Killed by her!

403
01:19:24,469 --> 01:19:28,890
The cursed video clip... it's her doing!

404
01:19:29,599 --> 01:19:32,393
No, it's not Nagi!

405
01:19:32,894 --> 01:19:37,398
Both she and her mother have evil blood!

406
01:19:37,482 --> 01:19:39,066
No, they don't!

407
01:19:41,027 --> 01:19:42,779
Before I die,

408
01:19:44,280 --> 01:19:45,406
I'll end her.

409
01:20:09,806 --> 01:20:11,015
Nagi?

410
01:20:16,270 --> 01:20:19,732
Is Mom here?

411
01:20:24,320 --> 01:20:25,488
Why?

412
01:20:26,280 --> 01:20:30,117
Why can't I see Mom?

413
01:20:56,686 --> 01:20:58,104
Nagi.

414
01:21:02,483 --> 01:21:04,443
Let's go see her.

415
01:22:21,604 --> 01:22:22,980
Mom...?

416
01:23:01,560 --> 01:23:03,396
Nagi...

417
01:23:05,982 --> 01:23:08,359
I'm glad you came.

418
01:24:47,875 --> 01:24:50,002
No...

419
01:24:55,925 --> 01:24:58,302
Mom...

420
01:25:01,514 --> 01:25:04,308
Now, it's over.

421
01:25:09,522 --> 01:25:09,939
Nagi!

422
01:25:54,483 --> 01:25:57,403
Nagi...

423
01:26:03,617 --> 01:26:05,703
Nagi...

424
01:26:25,723 --> 01:26:27,975
Nagi!

425
01:26:30,978 --> 01:26:32,021
Nagi!

426
01:27:13,979 --> 01:27:15,064
Nagi!

427
01:27:18,901 --> 01:27:22,905
Nagi!

428
01:29:03,714 --> 01:29:06,216
Auntie...

429
01:29:11,972 --> 01:29:14,308
Nagi.

430
01:29:38,832 --> 01:29:40,542
Do it again.

431
01:29:41,794 --> 01:29:42,795
Ready?

432
01:30:12,658 --> 01:30:16,245
I want you to witness my death.

433
01:30:19,581 --> 01:30:21,333
It's not really death

434
01:30:21,417 --> 01:30:23,752
unless witnessed by others.

435
01:30:25,754 --> 01:30:29,383
And what you've told me,

436
01:30:29,466 --> 01:30:31,552
I finally understand.

437
01:30:37,224 --> 01:30:42,563
Death is merely a passing point.

438
01:30:47,192 --> 01:30:48,527
That's right,

439
01:30:50,070 --> 01:30:51,947
death is merely a passing point.

440
01:30:52,614 --> 01:30:57,411
You can control the world
more after death than when alive.

441
01:31:07,588 --> 01:31:11,258
The seed of despair is growing,

442
01:31:11,925 --> 01:31:15,512
